layout: base.njk
title: Forms & Requests
permalink: /forms/
description: New-owner registration, owner contact updates, architectural (ACC) requests, maintenance reports, and records requests.
---
<p class="lead">Use these options to submit a request to the Association. No Google account or sign-in is required for the online forms.</p>

<div class="cards">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>New owner registration</h2>
    <p>Just bought a unit? Register with the Association so you receive assessment statements and required notices.</p>
    <p><a class="btn" href="{{ site.forms.newOwner }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the form →</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Update owner contact info</h2>
    <p>Keep your mailing address, phone, and email current with the Association, as your governing documents require. You may also set your notice preferences here.</p>
    <p><a class="btn" href="{{ site.forms.contactUpdate }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the form →</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Architectural / ACC request</h2>
    <p>Request approval for exterior modifications, additions, or design changes <em>before</em> starting work. Review the <a href="/reading/04-design-guidelines-v2/">Design Guidelines</a> first.</p>
    <p class="note">Email: <a href="mailto:{{ site.email.support }}?subject=ACC%20Request">{{ site.email.support }}</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Member / issue report</h2>
    <p>Report a common-area maintenance issue or community concern.</p>
    <p class="note">Email: <a href="mailto:{{ site.email.support }}?subject=Member%20Issue%20Report">{{ site.email.support }}</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Records inspection request</h2>
    <p>Owners (or an owner's designated agent, attorney, or CPA) may request to inspect or copy certain Association records under Tex. Prop. Code <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.1141" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.1141</a>.</p>
    <p><a class="btn" href="{{ site.forms.recordsRequest }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Start a records request →</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Resale certificate / transfer request</h2>
    <p>Selling or transferring a unit? Owners, agents, and title companies can request the resale certificate and statement of account required by Tex. Prop. Code <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.157" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.157</a>.</p>
    <p><a class="btn" href="{{ site.forms.resaleRequest }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Request a resale certificate →</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>General contact</h2>
    <p>Any other question for the Association or Board.</p>
    <p class="note">Email: <a href="mailto:{{ site.email.board }}">{{ site.email.board }}</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="callout statute">
  <p style="margin:0"><span class="k">Records requests.</span> Owners have a statutory right to inspect and copy certain books and records of the Association. The Association responds within the timeframes set by Texas Property Code <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.1141" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.1141</a> and withholds records that are confidential by law — for example, another owner's personal, financial, or violation information, and privileged legal matters.</p>
</div>
